properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 9 at 3:48AM CST until February 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW EXPECTED ACROSS CENTRAL AND EAST-CENTRAL WISCONSIN
TODAY...

.A low pressure system located over extreme southeast South Dakota
early this morning will track to northeast Iowa by noon, then
along the Wisconsin/Illinois border this afternoon. This is a
rather compact but vigorous storm system, and will bring a
significant snowfall to all but far northern Wisconsin. The storm
is also fast moving, so snow will quickly overspread the area
during the morning, but also diminish quickly from west to east
during the late afternoon and evening.

Although winds are not expected to be strong during the storm, the
heavy snowfall could reduce the visibility to under 1/4 mile at
times, especially in central and east-central Wisconsin. This will
likely result in hazardous travel conditions. Air travel is also
likely to be affected by the storm.

* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 10
inches, with the lower totals occurring north of Green Bay.

* WHERE...Portions of east-central and northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel will become difficult due to snow covered roads
and greatly reduced visibility in the heavy snow.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow is expected to develop between 800 am
and 1100 am, and will quickly become heavy. The rapid onset of
heavy snow is likely to result in very rapidly deteriorating
travel conditions during the middle to late morning.
properties.instruction:
If traveling during the storm, expect to drive at a much slower
than normal speed and allow plenty of time to reach your
destination. Be sure to take some food and water along with you in
your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road conditions
can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
